Date: Fri 11 May 2018
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2018; 31(20) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=26600


Infectious haematopoietic necrosis, Italy
-----------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 11 May 2018 from Dr Silvio Borrello, Chief Veterinary Officer, Food Safety and Collegial Bodies for Health Protection, [Ministry of Health], Department for Veterinary Public Health, Rome, Italy

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 17 Apr 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 8 May 2018
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 15 Oct 2015
Manifestation of disease: Sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: Infectious haematopoietic necrosis virus
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (NHI_TN_2018_1): Tenno, Trento, Trento [Trentino-Alto Adige]
Date of start of the outbreak: 17 Apr 2018
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Water type: fresh water
Population type: farmed
Production system: semi-closed
Total animals affected:
Species / Morbidity / Mortality / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Rainbow trout (_Oncorhynchus mykiss_) / 0 (scale 0 to 5) / 0 (scale 0 to 5)/ 80 000 / 3 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Rainbow trout (_Oncorhynchus mykiss_) / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: The outbreak was ascertained in the framework of the controls for the recognition of indemnity of infectious haematopoietic necrosis in the farm. No clinical signs have been observed; the outbreak was confirmed solely on the basis of laboratory results.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; zoning; disinfection; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: stamping out

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Experimental Zooprophylactic Institute (IZSVe), Padova (national laboratory) / rainbow trout (_Oncorhynchus mykiss_) / pathogen isolation on cell culture / 8 May 2018 / Positive
Experimental Zooprophylactic Institute (IZSVe), Padova (national laboratory) / rainbow trout (_Oncorhynchus mykiss_) / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 8 May 2018 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

